===History===
{{See also|Ghana national football team manager}}
[[File:Ghana national team u-21.JPG|thumb|Mali vs Ghana, exhibition game at Paris, 31 March 2015]]
Since 1957, the Ghanaian national football team has had 32 different [[head coach]]es and 3 [[Caretaker manager|caretaker]]s. [[Charles Gyamfi|C. K. Gyamfi]] led the Black Stars to 3 Africa Cup of Nations titles&nbsp;– in [[1963 African Cup of Nations|1963]], [[1965 African Cup of Nations|1965]] and [[1982 African Cup of Nations|1982]]&nbsp;– making Gyamfi the "joint most successful coach" in the competition's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanafa.org/news/200802/2603.php|title=C.K. Gyamfi picks CAF award|work=ghanafa.org|publisher=[[Ghana Football Association]] (GFA)|date=2 February 2008|access-date=11 February 2014|archive-date=22 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222145408/http://www.ghanafa.org/news/200802/2603.php|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Fred Osam-Duodu|Fred Osam Duodu]] led the Black Stars to their [[1978 Africa Cup of Nations]] title;<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://graphic.com.gh/sports/football/13359-reminiscences-50-years-after-ghana-s-first-ever-african-cup-of-nations-triumph.html|location=Accra, Ghana|title=Reminiscences! 50 years after Ghana's first ever African Cup of Nations triumph|first=Thomas|last=Frreman Yeboah|date=2 December 2013|access-date=11 February 2014|archive-date=22 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150122170829/http://graphic.com.gh/sports/football/13359-reminiscences-50-years-after-ghana-s-first-ever-african-cup-of-nations-triumph.html|url-status=live|newspaper=[[Daily Graphic]]}}</ref> [[Ratomir Dujković]], [[Milovan Rajevac]], [[James Kwesi Appiah]] and [[Otto Addo]] have led the Black Stars to World Cup qualification,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanafa.org/pages/blackstars/201204/7047.php|title=Appiah becomes 41st coach of the Black Stars|work=ghanafa.org|publisher=[[Ghana Football Association]] (GFA)|date=17 April 2012|access-date=11 February 2014|archive-date=22 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222145511/http://www.ghanafa.org/pages/blackstars/201204/7047.php|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Kwesi Appiah challenges his former bosses statistically">{{cite web|url=http://allsports.com.gh/2013/10/17/kwesi-appiah-challenges-his-former-bosses-statistically/|title=Kwesi Appiah challenges his former bosses statistically|publisher=allsports.com.gh|first=Fiifi|last=Anaman|date=17 October 2013|access-date=11 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222005446/http://allsports.com.gh/2013/10/17/kwesi-appiah-challenges-his-former-bosses-statistically/|archive-date=22 February 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> with the first two being [[Serbia|Serbs]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mumuni |first=Lukman |date=2022-10-05 |title=Serbian Coach Milovan Rajevac Eyes Black Stars Return, Insists He Has Unfinished Business With Ghana |url=https://sportsbrief.com/football/25151-serbian-coach-milovan-rajevac-eyes-black-stars-return-insists-unfinished-business-ghana/ |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=SportsBrief - Sport news. |language=en |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616195348/https://sportsbrief.com/football/25151-serbian-coach-milovan-rajevac-eyes-black-stars-return-insists-unfinished-business-ghana/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ex-Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac calls for unity ahead of World Cup |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/ex-ghana-coach-milovan-rajevac-calls-for-unity-ahead-of-world-cup |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Ghana Soccer Net dot com |date=5 October 2022 |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616195348/https://ghanasoccernet.com/ex-ghana-coach-milovan-rajevac-calls-for-unity-ahead-of-world-cup |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=4 October 2022 |title=Milovan Rajevac calls for Black Stars unity as World Cup looms |url=https://myjoyonline.com/milovan-rajevac-calls-for-black-stars-unity-as-world-cup-looms/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616195350/https://myjoyonline.com/milovan-rajevac-calls-for-black-stars-unity-as-world-cup-looms/ |archive-date=16 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=myjoyonline.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=22 September 2022 |title='Africa's Brazil' yet to beat Samba boys in 3 meetings – Tale of the tape |url=https://myjoyonline.com/africas-brazil-yet-to-beat-samba-boys-in-3-meetings-tale-of-the-tape |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616195348/https://myjoyonline.com/africas-brazil-yet-to-beat-samba-boys-in-3-meetings-tale-of-the-tape |archive-date=16 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=myjoyonline.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=11 November 2020 |title=The Black Stars 10 – No 1, Asamoah Gyan – A global icon made for big occasions |url=https://myjoyonline.com/the-black-stars-10-no-1-asamoah-gyan-a-global-icon-made-for-big-occasions |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616195350/https://myjoyonline.com/the-black-stars-10-no-1-asamoah-gyan-a-global-icon-made-for-big-occasions |archive-date=16 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=myjoyonline.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-06-09 |title=Stephen Appiah names 2006 World Cup squad as favourite Ghana team |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2020/06/09/stephen-appiah-names-2006-world-cup-squad-as-favourite-ghana-team/ |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Citi Sports Online |language=en-US |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616200644/https://citisportsonline.com/2020/06/09/stephen-appiah-names-2006-world-cup-squad-as-favourite-ghana-team/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-04-27 |title=Unfinished Business: Goran 'Plavi' Stevanovic wants Black Stars return |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2020/04/27/unfinished-business-goran-plavi-stevanovic-wants-black-stars-return/ |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Citi Sports Online |language=en-US |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616200645/https://citisportsonline.com/2020/04/27/unfinished-business-goran-plavi-stevanovic-wants-black-stars-return/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 October 2025 |title="It was our only chance to redeem ourselves" - Ghana celebrate qualification for FIFA World Cup 2026 |url=https://www.olympics.com/en/news/ghana-celebrate-qualification-for-fifa-world-cup-2026 |access-date=25 May 2026 |website=Olympics}}</ref> [[Carlos Queiroz|Carlos Quieroz]] was appointed in April 2026 as Ghana's head coach ahead of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], replacing [[Otto Addo]] after a run of four consecutive losses which culminated in a loss to the German national team in [[MHPArena|Stuttgart]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 April 2026 |title=Ghana names Carlos Queiroz as coach ahead of FIFA World Cup |url=https://www.africanews.com/2026/04/14/ghana-names-carlos-queiroz-as-coach-ahead-of-fifa-world-cup/ |access-date=24 May 2026 |website=Africanews |language=en-GB }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=30 March 2026 |title=Germany 2-1 Ghana: Undav scores winner in Stuttgart friendly |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cx2epz219d2t |access-date=25 May 2026 |website=BBC |language=en-GB}}</ref>Former Ghana international Anthony Yeboah later expressed support for Queiroz's squad selection ahead of the tournament, backing the coach's decisions for the 2026 FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{cite web |title=Anthony Yeboah backs Carlos Queiroz’s World Cup Black Stars squad selection |url=https://footy-africa.com/anthony-yeboah-backs-carlos-queirozs-world-cup-black-stars-squad-selection/ |website=Footy-Africa |date=2026-06-02 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

