==Competitive record==

===FIFA World Cup===
{{main|Ghana at the FIFA World Cup}}

[[File:Black Stars (World Cup).jpg|thumb|right|280px|Top: At the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] in Germany.<br/> Center and bottom: Ghana against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 tournament]] at [[Soccer City]], [[Johannesburg]], South Africa.]]
Ghana have qualified for 5 [[FIFA World Cup]] tournaments, in [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]], [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]], [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]] and [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026]]. In 2006, it was the only African side to advance to the [[2006 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|second round]] in Germany, and was the sixth nation in a row from Africa to progress beyond the group stages of the World Cup.<ref name="Ghana 2-1 USA">{{cite news | date=22 June 2006 | url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4853408.stm | title=Ghana 2–1 USA | publisher=[[BBC]] | access-date=29 February 2012 | archive-date=16 January 2009 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090116035657/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4853408.stm | url-status=live }}</ref> Ghana had the youngest team in the [[2006 FIFA World Cup squads#Ghana|2006 edition]] with an average age of 23 years and 352 days,<ref name="Ghana 2-1 USA"/> and were praised for their improving performance.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/aboutfifa/organisation/news/newsid=106133/index.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002174229/http://www.fifa.com/aboutfifa/organisation/news/newsid=106133/index.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2 October 2013 | title= Rehhagel: Africa is catching up |date=13 September 2006 | publisher=[[FIFA|Fédération Internationale de Football Association]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid=104682.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430044305/http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid=104682.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=30 April 2011 | title= Black Stars Ascend To Glory  | publisher=[[FIFA|Fédération Internationale de Football Association]] |date=27 July 2006 }}</ref> [[FIFA]] ranked Ghana 13th out of the 32 countries who competed in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.myradiogoldlive.com/index.php/articles/4432-amazing-black-stars-set-eyes-on-brazil-2014 | title= Amazing Black Stars Set Eyes on Brazil 2014 | work= Radio Gold 90.5 |date=16 October 2013  | access-date= 23 November 2013 | archive-date= 2 December 2013 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131202231111/http://www.myradiogoldlive.com/index.php/articles/4432-amazing-black-stars-set-eyes-on-brazil-2014 | url-status= unfit }}</ref>

In the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 World Cup]], Ghana reached the [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Uruguay vs Ghana|quarter-finals]] where they were eliminated by [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], after [[Luis Suárez]]'s handball prevented a possible winning goal.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2010/matches/match_58/default.stm | title=Uruguay 1–1 Ghana (4–2 pens) | work=BBC Sport | access-date=29 February 2012 | author=Fletcher, Paul | archive-date=9 November 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109013011/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/world_cup_2010/matches/match_58 | url-status=live }}</ref> Of the 32 countries that participated in the 2010 edition, FIFA ranked Ghana 7th.<ref>{{cite news | date=13 July 2010 | url=http://www.ghanafa.org/blackstars/201007/4902.php | title=Ghana records best World Cup ranking | work=ghanafa.org | publisher=[[Ghana Football Association]] (GFA) | access-date=28 February 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120109025239/http://ghanafa.org/blackstars/201007/4902.php | archive-date=9 January 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref>

After beating [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] 7–3 on aggregate in November 2013, Ghana qualified for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news | date=19 November 2013 |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2225273/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131120004419/http://www.fifa.com//worldcup/preliminaries/news/newsid=2225273/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=20 November 2013| title=Ghana qualify, Egypt go down fighting | work= fifa.com | publisher=[[FIFA]] | access-date=9 December 2013}}</ref> For the first time, Ghana were eliminated in the group stage, drawing 2–2 against Germany, and losing to the United States and Portugal 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186476/match-report.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628205703/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186476/match-report.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 June 2014|title=Ronaldo downs Ghana but Portugal crash out|work=FIFA.com| date=26 June 2014| access-date=26 June 2014}}</ref> Eight years later, Ghana failed to advance past the group stage again, at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/en/articles/fwc-world-cup-qatar-2022-ayew-kudus-amartey|title=Black Stars dimmed as penalty pain resurfaces|date=2 December 2022|access-date=2 December 2022|work=FIFA.com}}</ref>

