===Africa Cup of Nations===
{{main|Ghana at the Africa Cup of Nations}}

[[File:ACON_2015_GHA_GUI_(16511976922).jpg|thumb|right|278x278px|At the 2015 AFCON vs. Guinea in the quarter-finals.]]
The ''Black Stars'' of Ghana have won the Africa Cup of Nations four times: in [[1963 African Cup of Nations|1963]], [[1965 African Cup of Nations|1965]], [[1978 African Cup of Nations|1978]], and [[1982 African Cup of Nations|1982]], bettered only by [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] and [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]]. As the first winner of three AFCON tournaments, Ghana obtained the right to permanently hold the trophy in 1978.<ref name="BBC-Newtrophy">{{cite news|url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/1562471.stm|author=BBC News| publisher=[[BBC]]| title=Nations Cup trophy revealed | access-date=16 March 2007| date=25 September 2001| archive-date=26 May 2022| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220526023346/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/1562471.stm| url-status=live}}</ref>

In November 2024, following a 1–1 draw against [[Angola national football team|Angola]], Ghana failed to qualify for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|2025 AFCON]], missing the tournament for the first time since 2004.<ref>{{cite news |date=15 November 2024 |title=Ghana fail to reach AFCON for 1st time since '04 |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/42412488/ghana-fail-qualify-afcon-africa-cup-nations |access-date=16 November 2024 |website=ESPN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Mintah |first=Yaw Loic |date=18 November 2024 |title=2025 AFCON Qualifiers: Ghana ends campaign winless in abysmal and disappointing fashion |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2024/11/2025-afcon-qualifiers-ghana-ends-campaign-winless-in-abysmal-and-disappointing-fashion/ |access-date=19 November 2024 |website=Citi Sports Online}}</ref>

